Five days after being sworn in as governor of Lagos State, Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Monday recorded a major first as he signed into law the state’s 2019 budget of N873,532,460,725 prepared by his predecessor, Akinwunmi Ambode, promising a speedy implementation. The budget consists of N393,841,387 recurrent expenditure or 45 percent, and N479,691,730,705 capital expenditure, representing 55…